info.author: Albert Alvarez Bruned
info.description:
reportjira Package

to install:  
pip3 install reportjira  

ReportJira is a GUI application to inform Atlassian Jira of all tasks performed during the day, sending Worklogs to JIRA tikets.
Once it is executed, it requests a YAML file that must follow specific guidelines that are easy to implement.

'pathImages' is the path where the images will be.  
'usernameJira' is Jira username (email)  
'tokenJira' is Jira token (https://id.atlassian.com/manage/api-tokens)  
'domainJira' is the domain path (example: 'myjira.atlassian.net')  
'data' is the buttons configuration  

Make rows as you need, but continuing for each row as in the example, from row0.  
For each button you can configure the id of the Atlassian Jira ticket to report, and its respective icon.  

You now can report to Atlassian Jira setting username, password and jira domain, and de data buttons in YAML file  

An example of 'data-work.yaml':
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/alvarezbruned/reportjira/master/README.md
